Preheat grill pan (or grill). Form ground beef into four patties (wash hands); season with salt and pepper. Place patties in grill pan (or on grill); grill 3-4 minutes on each side or until 160 degrees F. Top with cheese and let stand to melt. Combine horseradish dip and sauce; spread 2 tablespoons sauce mixture on inside of buns. Place burgers on bottom halves of buns; top each with 1/2 cup spinach, 2 slices bacon, and tomato. Serve.